						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājakēśarivarman, Year 14 = c. 10th Century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription registers an endowment of 20 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, by Muri Kāmakkanār, the wife of Iḷangōnaḍikaḷ, for feeding 20 brāhmaṇas on the day of Ārdra every month, for the merit of one Ēkavīra-Divākaradēvar. A body called <hi rend="italic">Tiruvāthirai-gaṇapperumakkaḷ</hi> accepted this gift.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII No. 244.]</p>						

						</summary>
